====Translations====
*Icelandic: [[flís]]

===Verb===
'''mote'''

# to [[embarass]] or [[patronize]] either with or without malice, especially in a case of situational [[irony]]; short for [[demote]]; "''And as Elizabeth tripped Frank--causing him to drop his soda--Andrew, who was looking on happily, shouted, "Moted!"''"

===Verbal Auxiliary===
'''mote'''
From Olde English ''mOtan'' meaning "to be allowed to"

# must; "''So mote it be!''"

